latestPosts.caption:
Does your skin also bounce back? ☺️
You can use this simple nighttime routine to achieve healthy, glowing skin. The products I have used are linked in my story and highlight *links*

Names:

Johnson’s Baby Oil & Cetaphil Cleanser: For double cleansing, I use Johnson’s Baby Oil because it suits my skin, is safe to use, and works wonders in removing makeup. This is followed by Cetaphil Gentle Cleanser, which is mild and removes leftover dirt and excess oil.

Laneige Cream Skin Ceramide: I started using it lately, and I can’t say much about it yet, but it has a very lightweight, milk-like formula. I have used The Face Shop Rice and Ceramide, and after using this for a month, I’ll decide whether to switch to this one or stick with the previous product.

Plum Rice Water and Niacinamide Serum: Rice water brightens, moisturizes, and reduces irritation in the skin. Simultaneously, Niacinamide evens skin tone and reduces pores, dark spots, and acne scars.

Advanced Snail 96 Mucin Power Essence: It’s one of my favorites, and I also have the moisturizer of the same line. I’ve been using it for the past year, and it helps the skin prevent and repair damages, filling the skin with elasticity for a healthier, younger-looking appearance.

Jade face Roller: It helps stimulate collagen in the skin, leading to collagen remodeling.

M Caffeine Under Eye Cream: This product has helped people with dark circles so much, and I can say this with assurance because my sister and three of my friends have seen visible differences in their dark circles. You’ll have to use it regularly and will see a difference within up to six weeks.

Dot and Key Lip Balm (Cherry Pop): Dry and chapped lips are common in winters. You can clearly see the difference in the video before and after applying this product. It provides hydration to your lips.

If there are any questions, you can drop them in the comments.❤️
